.TH "gfs2_alloc_extent" 9 "gfs2_alloc_extent" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gfs2_alloc_extent \- allocate an extent from a given bitmap
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" gfs2_alloc_extent
.BI "(const struct gfs2_rbm *rbm "  ","
.BI "bool dinode "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *n "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rbm" 12
the resource group information
.IP "dinode" 12
TRUE if the first block we allocate is for a dinode
.IP "n" 12
The extent length (value/result)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Add the bitmap buffer to the transaction.
Set the found bits to \fInew_state\fP to change block's allocation state.
